==English==
===Etymology===
Named "slam book" because when a teacher would come near, the book would be slammed shut and covered with homework, papers, or other appropriate camouflage. 

===Noun===
'''[[slam]] [[book]]'''
{{wikipedia}}
#traditionally a [[notebook]] passed from student to student in which questions are written and answered [[anonymous]]ly. Questions often focus on such issues as which girl is most [[popular]], who is a dog, and which teacher is the worst dressed.